{"title":"Pirelli Rolls Out Tubeless Four-Season P Zero Race 4S TLR Tires","link":"https://bikerumor.com/pirelli-rolls-out-tubeless-four-season-p-zero-race-4s-tlr-tires/","date":1683143395000,"content":"<p>Pirellis’ all-arounder race tire, the P Zero Race 4S, is now tubeless-ready and ready to ship. For those unfamiliar, the tire is the middle ground between the full-on race <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pirelli-make-p-zero-race-tlr-road-tires-24-percent-faster/\" target=\"_blank\">P Zero TLR</a> and the performance training-focused <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-pirelli-cinturato-tubeless-ready-road-tires-take-on-the-strade-bianche/\" target=\"_blank\">Cinturato Velo.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/PPirellis-P-Zero-Race-4Sside-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"424\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/PPirellis-P-Zero-Race-4Sside--800x424.jpeg\" alt=\"Pirellis P Zero Race 4Sside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/PPirellis-P-Zero-Race-4Sside--800x424.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/PPirellis-P-Zero-Race-4Sside--297x157.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/PPirellis-P-Zero-Race-4Sside--120x64.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/PPirellis-P-Zero-Race-4Sside--768x407.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/PPirellis-P-Zero-Race-4Sside-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is it — Pirelli P Zero Race 4S TLR</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Pirelli P Zero Race 4S TLR is an updated four-season tire from the Italian tire powerhouse. Previously only available in tube-type tires, the new Pirelli P Zero Race 4S TLR is tubeless and hookless rim compatible.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses--800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Pirellis P Zero Race 4S uses\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses--800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses--297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses--120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses--768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses--400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses--1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-uses-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The four-season compound offers performance, reliability, and a lively road feel thanks to a 120 TPI nylon casing and nylon breaker to increase puncture protection.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-tread-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"529\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-tread--800x529.jpeg\" alt=\"Pirellis P Zero Race 4S tread\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-tread--800x529.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-tread--297x196.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-tread--120x79.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-tread--768x508.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-tread-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new P Zero Race 4S TLR is produced in Pirellis’ Milano-Bollate facility in Northern Italy, along with others in the Pirelli cycling line.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2><br />Details — Pirelli P Zero Race 4S TLR</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-casing-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"634\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-casing--800x634.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-casing--800x634.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-casing--297x235.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-casing--120x95.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-casing--768x609.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-casing-.jpeg 878w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>SmartNET Silica Compound</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The tread of the Pirelli P Zero Race 4S TLR is made with the SmartNET Silica compound, the same used in the Cinturato Velo tire. The compound is a mix of materials and differs from traditional silica, best known for its grip and performance in wet and cold conditions. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Pirelli explains, “SmartNET Silica compound creates a product with outstanding qualities on wet and typical cold-weather surfaces…its natural chemical affinity for water, and more generally, with low temperatures.”</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-weight-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"338\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-weight--800x338.jpeg\" alt=\"Pirellis P Zero Race 4S weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-weight--800x338.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-weight--297x126.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-weight--120x51.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-weight--768x325.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-weight-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Speed Core Technology</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Pirelli P Zero Race 4S TLR is equipped internally with Speed Core Technology. The compound has low rolling resistance and offers increased protection against punctures. The compound was first employed in the Pirelli P Zero Race TLR and is a mainstay in Pirelli performance tires.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Sizing and Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"153\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-800x153.jpeg\" alt=\"Pirellis P Zero Race 4S weights\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-800x153.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-297x57.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-120x23.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S-768x147.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Pirellis-P-Zero-Race-4S.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Pirelli P Zero Race 4S TLR is currently available in 28, 30, and 32mm widths with black side walls. We hope to have a review set arriving soon and will report back with a full review.<br /><em>For more information, check out; <a href=\"https://www.pirelli.com/tyres/en-ww/bike/tyres/catalogue/p-zero-race-tlr-4s\" target=\"_blank\">Pirelli.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pirelli-rolls-out-tubeless-four-season-p-zero-race-4s-tlr-tires/\">Pirelli Rolls Out Tubeless Four-Season P Zero Race 4S TLR Tires</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"76365adcddbedfba07ba1d8eaa22c203b075c7a139640a5427be56bd7948ff26","category":"Cycling"}